The paper deals with cryptographic protocols and their computational complexity, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) the most likely category. The use of linear algebraic techniques suggests cs.IT (Information Theory) as a possible category. The paper also involves the analysis of algorithms, which could place it in cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Finally, the use of algebraic structures and techniques could also make cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) a possible category.
